  "prompt": "What are the branch options for 7k rank holders in manipal institute of technology entrance exam?",
  "response": "For candidates with a rank of around 7,000 score in the Manipal Institute of Technology (MIT) entrance exam (MET), the branch options may vary based on the competition and seat availability for that particular year. Here\u2019s a general idea of the branches that might be available at this rank:\n\n### **Likely Available Branches (2023 Trends):**\n1. **Civil Engineering**  \n2. **Chemical Engineering**  \n3. **Biotechnology**  \n4. **Industrial and Production Engineering**  \n5. **Aerospace Engineering**  \n6. **Mechanical Engineering (later rounds, if available)**  \n7. **Mechatronics Engineering**  \n8. **Automobile Engineering**\n\n### **Less Likely (but possible in later rounds):**\n1. **Electronics and Communication Engineering (ECE)**  \n2. **Electrical and Electronics Engineering (EEE)**  \n3. **Computer Science and Engineering (CSE)**  \n4. **Information Technology (IT)**  \n\n### **Key Points to Note:**\n- Higher-demand branches like **Aerospace**, **Mechanical**, **ECE**, **EEE**, and **CSE** may be limited at this rank but could open up in later rounds of counselling as students withdraw or change their preferences.\n- **Biotechnology** and **Civil Engineering** are often more accessible at this rank.\n- Seat availability depends on the number of candidates, their preferences, and the cutoff trends for the year.\n\n### **Next Steps:**\n1. **Counselling Process**: Participate in the MET counselling process and keep track of seat allotments.\n2. **Branch Options**: Be flexible and prioritize branches based on your interests and career goals.\n3. **Waitlist**: If your desired branch is not available initially, you may have a chance in subsequent rounds as seats open up.\n\nIt\u2019s advisable to check the latest cutoff trends and counselling updates from the official MIT website or contact the institute directly for accurate information.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
